param.dialogReference: Output point feature class containing the lowest points returned by the tool.

tool.summary: Finds the lowest point (or points if several have the same elevation) of the input surface within a defined area.
tool.usage:
• This tool requires Spatial Analyst.

  • The output may contain more than one lowest point.

  • The output contains a field named elevation with the elevation value of the lowest point.

  • The units of the lowest elevation point are in the z (elevation) units of the Input Surface. Check the Input Surface's metadata for this unit.
